right bar: \n   \n Double-click on one of the items, and you will be directed to the Deployment section of the Model Browser, where you can see your new deployment scripts at the end of the list, alongside all previously created scripts: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/1/142f467a8c0c1acd93eee481a4676beeac4c1de5.png]\nDescription: The image presents a Model Browser interface related to a software application named \u0022myapplication.\u0022 It displays a hierarchical view under the \u0022Common\u0022 section, specifically within the \u0022Deployment\u0022 category. The tree structure includes entities such as \u0022Database_Entity_Priority,\u0022 \u0022Database_Entity_Task,\u0022 and \u0022Database_Entity_Status,\u0022 each with associated tasks and fields. Key elements are listed with identifiers such as \u002200140_Database_Entity_Project\u0022 and \u002200150_Database_Entity_Project,\u0022 which are highlighted in teal, indicating their importance. Additionally, versions are noted, with the application version marked as \u00221.0.0.\u0022 This interface is likely designed for managing database entities and their relationships within the application architecture.\n\n\n  \n If you want to view or edit the script before executing it, double-click on its name to open it in the editor. There, you can review the following: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/8/84c99d1ba3b29ac48e6bb19f75c18bdc0f9f7ce7.png]\nDescription: Service Command Update Activity interface presents the command \u002200140_Database_Entity_Project\u0022. The visible fields include Name (\u002200140_Database_Entity_Project\u0022), Order (140), Service (DataService), and Platform (MsSql). The Command section displays an SQL command for creating a table named \u0022Project\u0022, with columns such as Name (NVarChar(100)), Description (nvarchar(max)), Start (DateTime), End (DateTime), Responsible_Id (UniqueIdentifier), RecordCreated (DateTime), RecordUpdatedBy (UniqueIdentifier), Id (UniqueIdentifier, PRIMARY KEY, NONCLUSTERED), and RecordUpdated (DateTime). The command uses standard SQL syntax for defining a database schema.\n\n\n  \n This is the table creation script. The other script defines the foreign key: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/6/675a902200ffae94e8b42dfb38ebb096104c7fa4.png]\nDescription: Service Command Update Activity titled \u002200150_Database_Entity_Project\u0022 is displayed. The interface includes fields labeled \u0022Name\u0022 with the value \u002200150_Database_Entity_Project,\u0022 \u0022Order\u0022 set to \u0022150,\u0022 \u0022Service\u0022 indicating \u0022DataService,\u0022 and \u0022Platform\u0022 labeled as \u0022MsSql.\u0022 The command section contains SQL code: \u0022ALTER TABLE [Project] ADD CONSTRAINT [FK_Project_Responsible_Id_BusinessPartner] FOREIGN KEY ([Responsible_Id]) REFERENCES [BusinessPartner] ([Id]);\u0022 indicating the addition of a foreign key constraint to the \u0022Project\u0022 table, referencing the \u0022BusinessPartner\u0022 table.\n\n\n  \n   Script Execution \n Scripts must be executed in the order in which they were created, which you can identify by the script numbering: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/d/d16b2a5257437825d6b603341cd5523fbb5a7255.png]\nDescription: The image displays a section of a data structure representing a software application, labeled as \u0022myapplication\u0022 with a version number \u00221.0.0.\u0022 It includes a list of database entities and fields, with visible entries highlighted in red. The visible UI text consists of several identifiers followed by their respective labels: \u002200010 Database_Entity_Priority,\u0022 \u002200020 Database_Entity_Task,\u0022 \u002200030 Database_Field_Task.Priority_Id,\u0022 \u002200040 Database_Entity_FK_Task_Priority_Id_Priority,\u0022 \u002200050 Database_Entity_Status,\u0022 \u002200060 Database_Field_Priority.Name,\u0022 \u002200070 Database_Field_Priority.Order,\u0022 \u002200090 Database_Field_Task.AssignedTo_Id,\u0022 \u002200100 Database_Field_Task.DueDate,\u0022 and \u002200110 Database_Field_Task.Description.\u0022 This structure appears to be part of a database schema, likely intended for managing task priorities and related entities.\n\n\n  \n To execute a script, right-click its name and select  Execute  or press  Ctrl\u002BX : \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/4/489702710219f6c43b0a493665a93953c93242ec.png]\nDescription: The image displays a \u0022Model Browser\u0022 interface for an application named \u0022myapplication.","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-05-01T23:52:53"},"vector":[-0.043703448,-0.014285192,-0.06205811,0.024981128,-0.006872746,-0.032914378,-0.0018333343,0.010021803,0.013851339,0.014255466,-0.011009086,-0.016665252,-0.018181572,0.015063997,-0.00010388821,0.008475114,0.035620134,-0.0074903257,0.02159499,0.03631794,-0.03079556,-0.006803422,0.06411994,0.012309684,-0.012144014,0.01409229,-0.0035676174,-0.04496553,0.0024995075,0.021830592,0.031745188,-0.060007934,0.023197047,-0.049749386,-0.0070298263,-0.013313355,0.024340374,0.0023488197,-0.047944352,0.032566626,-0.018457862,0.017183216,-0.024067966,0.0146887945,0.013014576,-0.03214009,-0.004363453,-0.015379145,0.017081387,-0.0055693467,-0.05839151,-0.030435676,0.01580417,-0.019328915,0.031935897,0.043642882,-0.043078624,-0.0043716365,-0.06930578,0.022692736,-0.02548972,-0.002989126,0.019792533,-0.02755599,-0.006214405,0.0016860905,-0.011038969,0.0019297978,-0.010170685,-0.04414321,-0.012857794,0.023220297,-0.075484015,-0.033675488,-0.055473212,0.0265871,0.026543513,-0.01641668,-0.053218797,0.005401488,-0.02180918,-0.016481252,-0.009200257,0.011166354,0.009307262,0.019029114,-0.029721253,0.0501403,0.044186525,0.006801311,-0.01187202,-0.00023232876,0.0408982